00:00:06.633 --> 00:00:08.323
today we will make luchai.

00:00:08.651 --> 00:00:14.107
luchai is known as luchi in bengal and is a small poori made from maida

00:00:14.467 --> 00:00:17.141
it is prepared like that of plain poori.

00:00:17.510 --> 00:00:23.605
it is served with aloo masala at some place and halwa at some other places.

00:00:23.914 --> 00:00:26.207
let's start with the procedure of making luchai.

00:00:26.527 --> 00:00:27.789
we need:

00:00:28.013 --> 00:00:28.989
maida - 1 cup

00:00:29.467 --> 00:00:33.231
salt - 1/4 tsp or as per taste

00:00:33.621 --> 00:00:38.161
oil - to fry luchai and add in dough.

00:00:40.398 --> 00:00:42.398
knead dough first.

00:00:42.837 --> 00:00:51.225
add salt and 1/2 tbsp oil in pan.

00:01:02.907 --> 00:01:06.224
knead hard dough as required for making pori.

00:01:14.616 --> 00:01:16.132
add little water at a time

00:01:58.212 --> 00:02:01.902
grease your hands with some oil and knead the  dough.

00:02:02.891 --> 00:02:08.927
wehave used 1/3 cup of water or less then 1/2 cup

00:02:10.168 --> 00:02:16.358
dough is ready,now keep aside the dough for 15 minutes  so that it gets set.

00:02:27.703 --> 00:02:32.608
now make small balls from this dough.

00:02:49.652 --> 00:02:54.017
roll the balls and give them a shape of peda.

00:02:59.043 --> 00:03:00.892
oil is hot.

00:03:01.243 --> 00:03:04.323
now roll start rolling luchai.

00:03:10.436 --> 00:03:15.015
roll with 2.5 inch diameter poori.

00:03:21.123 --> 00:03:24.305
check whether oil is hot or not.

00:03:54.043 --> 00:03:57.631
press gently with ladle so that luchai puffs up.

00:04:04.506 --> 00:04:11.487
take out the fried luchai on plate with absorbent paper.

00:05:24.260 --> 00:05:26.553
piping hot luchai are ready.

00:05:26.785 --> 00:05:30.587
serve with aloo sabzi or sooji halwa.

